data.description: WELCOME!! This charming and modernized cozy cabin is nestled conveniently in the San Bernardino National Forest, just a short 15-minute drive up the mountain. Perfect for those who are seeking a close staycation away from home, or for those who need to travel to the City for work. This comfortable retreat is the epitome of mountain living, offering a unique blend of comfort and tranquility. As you step inside, you’ll be greeted by warm and inviting interior, and lots of natural sunlight beaming through the newer energy efficient windows!!  This home also offers a brand-new Service Panel, just installed!! Went from 1930s 60 AMP Fuse box to a 2023 200 AMP Circuit Breaker, which means it is more energy efficient and ready to charge your Electrical vehicle, Jacuzzi, you name it!! This homey-cabin features a quaint bedroom on the main floor and an additional loft space upstairs, that is easily used as another bedroom and/or office space. The kitchen offers a brand-new built-in stove-top and oven. Walk past the kitchen and bathroom and you will see this home offers a dedicated laundry room inside, so you don’t have to step outside the comfort of your home and don’t have to go to a basement. Take a step outside onto the nice, large wooden deck, where you are offered a serene space to enjoy your morning coffee, or an evening read by the fire and a pleasant seasonal creek that runs through your very own backyard! Whether you’re inside or out on the relaxing patio area, you’ll be treated to lovely, peaceful views of beautifully aged and radiant pine trees that line the lot, and you also have your own mature apple trees that will offer you plenty of tasty apples every season. This cabin is more than just a home; it’s a sanctuary where you can escape from the hustle and bustle of everyday life. Waters Drive is also well maintained during all seasons and always accessible. Here at 23035 Waters, you are steps away from a well-stocked local market that carries all your needs year-round, and also adjacent to the local post office and a nice 5-minute drive to the popular Lake Gregory!
